<br>
I have a lot of experience guild/raid leading as well.<br>
<br>
Anyway, two things I noticed above which may or may not be true but probably are:<br>
<br>
1) Clerics raid usefulness does not only sit with CH.  No CLR on a raid = no Kazad which is like 800 hp gone for every person, also no DI for the tanks, the combination of losing those 2 will put you *at least* half an expansion behind content your guild is capable of doing.  I welcome the end game GOD guilds to prove that paladin MTing something like RZ in time is doable with only druids in the CH chain.<br>
<br>
Note that most end game guilds plan/recruit around having 54 people per raid for GOD.  That means that the maximum they would be walking into time with is about 54, and since end gamers wont want to even go back to time most of that 54 probably wont even log on.  <br>
<br>
Reasonably, I dont think its doable, unless maybe arch overseers can talk their members into doing it.<br>
<br>
2) Also, correct me if I am wrong, I havent ever fought Quarm, but I believe the difficulty of that fight isnt really his massive melee DPS?  Thats why I mentioned RZ instead of Quarm above.<br>
<br>
I do also think bards get progressively worse in the high end game, they have too many caps in EQ that are too easy to reach and bards cant break enough of those caps enough to make a big enough difference.<br>
<br>
Btw, If a paladin had a lot of + shielding items those would only work versus the DB of the mob hits and not the DI, so stuff with a really large DI and low DB +shielding would be worse than +HP.  Lots of mobs follow the High DI Low DB formula, and I mean a lot.<br>
